<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Jones, John. Letter to Judge Adam Mabane, 1787, with a copy of Jones's testimony 1783. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0003</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">that shall increase his power, already too great, &amp; that shall authorise him to become a Juror, and thereby to distract and throw an odium on Juries, who are and ought to be a restraint upon him, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">is a fact of a very Serious</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">important Nature</span>.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Endless would be the Task if I was to give a History of all I could collect: I cease.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Most of these facts of such a <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Serious</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">important</span> &amp; <span class="DelHand-author">I will add</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">alarming</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Nature</span>, I know M<sup>r</sup> Judge Dunn to be a stranger to; for he was absent.  And I believe him and M<sup>r</sup> Judge Panet to be innocent of them all <span class="AddHand-author">for neither of them were challenged, nor did either of them offer</span> <span class="AddHand-author">to shew</span> <span class="AddHand-author">a Judgement to M</span><span class="AddHand-author"><sup>r</sup></span><span class="AddHand-author"> Gordon<span class="DelHand-author">s</span> a Spectator or</span> <span class="AddHand-author">Standerby.</span>  I am not conscious of any false representations in this address to you; If I err in any trivial point, I am ignorant of it; In essentials I know I do not err: I am substantially right.  You should be versed in the Law; I am amenable to it; you can appeal to it, and I stand forth <span class="AddHand-author">to answer</span> under the Signature of</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">John Jones</p>
<p>Quebec, 10<sup>th</sup> Novem<sup>r</sup> 1787.</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[14]</span></p>

